<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1437,222,607]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,258,283]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Scott" box="[284,499,258,283]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Scott" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref101992" refString="Scott, V. L., Ascher, J. S., Griswold, T. &amp; Nufio, C. R. (2011) The bees of Colorado (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Natural History Inventory of Colorado, 1 - 100." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Scott 
<emphasis box="[353,414,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that 
<typeStatus box="[637,685,259,283]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">type</typeStatus>
material of this species from 
<collectingRegion box="[1045,1149,258,283]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Colorado</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1212,1291,258,283]" country="United States of America" name="Illinois" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Illinois</collectingRegion>
may not be conspecific and could not confirm presence in 
<collectingRegion box="[690,794,294,319]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Colorado</collectingRegion>
of material matching 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1863" box="[1050,1155,294,319]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis box="[1050,1155,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">N. lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the eastern 
<collectingCountry name="United States of America" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">United States</collectingCountry>
as described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitchell" box="[406,583,330,355]" firstAuthor="Mitchell" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 557" refId="ref96606" refString="Mitchell, T. B. (1962) Bees of the Eastern United States: volume II. N. C. Agricultural Experimental Station Technical Bulletin, 152, 1 - 557." type="book chapter" year="1962">Mitchell (1962)</bibRefCitation>
and identified by that author. They therefore removed this species from the fully confirmed 
<collectingRegion box="[336,440,366,391]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Colorado</collectingRegion>
state list. However, the male 
<typeStatus box="[781,884,366,391]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">lectotype</typeStatus>
in the ANSP designated by Cresson (1916) was collected in Pikeâ€™s Peak, 
<collectingRegion box="[442,549,402,427]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Colorado</collectingRegion>
, making that occurrence correct by definition. The 
<typeStatus box="[1144,1192,403,427]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1863" box="[1308,1378,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis box="[1308,1378,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may prove to have been composite, and this would explain failure by 
<bibRefCitation author="Scott" box="[870,1069,438,463]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Scott" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref101992" refString="Scott, V. L., Ascher, J. S., Griswold, T. &amp; Nufio, C. R. (2011) The bees of Colorado (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Natural History Inventory of Colorado, 1 - 100." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Scott 
<emphasis box="[933,989,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
to confirm non-type 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1863" box="[1305,1375,438,463]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis box="[1305,1375,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[151,255,474,499]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Colorado</collectingRegion>
that match this species 
<emphasis box="[524,586,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mitchell" box="[593,770,474,499]" firstAuthor="Mitchell" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 557" refId="ref96606" refString="Mitchell, T. B. (1962) Bees of the Eastern United States: volume II. N. C. Agricultural Experimental Station Technical Bulletin, 152, 1 - 557." type="book chapter" year="1962">Mitchell (1962)</bibRefCitation>
and as identified by subsequent bee specialists working on the eastern fauna. If 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Mitchell (1962)" authorityName="Mitchell" authorityYear="1962" box="[386,713,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis box="[386,456,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">lepida</emphasis>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitchell" box="[535,713,510,535]" firstAuthor="Mitchell" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 557" refId="ref96606" refString="Mitchell, T. B. (1962) Bees of the Eastern United States: volume II. N. C. Agricultural Experimental Station Technical Bulletin, 152, 1 - 557." type="book chapter" year="1962">Mitchell (1962)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
do diverge from the 
<collectingRegion box="[955,1059,510,535]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Colorado</collectingRegion>
<typeStatus box="[1068,1174,510,535]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">lectotype</typeStatus>
, then populations from the eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[284,438,546,571]" name="United States of America" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">United States</collectingCountry>
, including 
<collectingRegion box="[568,678,546,571]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Michigan</collectingRegion>
, may require description as a new species unless another name is found to be applicable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
